				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No games ever actually use address bus B from the cartridge connector.<br /><br />It was a pretty bad bus. If you used it to send data, you wouldn't be able to DMA that data directly into VRAM (which is also exposed on the B bus), meaning you'd have to buffer it in WRAM, doubling your transfer overhead for any graphical data sent.<br /><br />The Satellaview and Exertainment Bike use bus B, but only by way of the expansion port (same bus, different location.)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

