					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Nobody knows how the S-DD1 realizes when to begin decompression.<br /><br />I simulate it by having the S-DD1 watch $4300-437f, which is decidedly not on the B-bus.<br /><br />It's possible that the CPU doesn't even propagate accesses to internal CPU registers to the cartridge A-bus, but it's the only way I can figure for it to work. There's nothing really on the B-bus that would be useful for what the S-DD1 is watching.</div>

